---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'How long does a typical build take?',
    a: 'Most internal apps ship a usable first version in 6 to 12 weeks. The variable is scope clarity, not engineering. Teams that come in with a clear workflow problem and a short list of must-haves launch faster; teams that need discovery first take longer up front and faster after.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What stack do you build on?',
    a: 'Modern, boring, and battle-tested. Typically a TypeScript and React-based front end, Node or Python on the server, Firebase for data and auth, hosted on Vercel or Render. The point of the stack is fast iteration and long-term maintainability, not novelty.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can it integrate with the tools we already use?',
    a: 'Yes. Most builds include integrations with at least one CRM, billing system, calendar, or third-party API on day one. If a tool has an API or webhook, we can wire it in. If it does not, we will tell you up front before scope is locked.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What happens after launch?',
    a: 'That depends on the engagement. Some teams want a finished build and a clean handover; most stay on a monthly partnership for ongoing changes, new features, and adjustments as their team grows. We structure it around what your team actually needs, not a fixed contract shape.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What if our team\'s needs change halfway through?',
    a: 'They will, and the build is designed for it. We work in small slices so you can change direction between sprints without scrapping work. Scope changes get re-quoted; pivots in priority within scope are free.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do we need to have everything figured out before we start?',
    a: 'No. If you did, you probably would not need us. We start with a discovery sprint to map your current workflow, then lock the first slice before writing production code. Most teams find clarity in the audit they did not have going in.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="relative bg-black py-24 text-white md:py-32">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-grid-dark opacity-30 [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,black_30%,transparent_75%)]"></div>
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-32 top-1/3 h-96 w-96 rounded-full bg-gold/10 blur-3xl"></div>

  <div class="container-x relative">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gold-soft">
        <span class="h-px w-6 bg-gold-soft"></span>
        FAQ
      </span>
      <h2 class="mt-5 font-display text-4xl font-medium leading-[1.05] tracking-tight md:text-6xl">
        Software questions, answered.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl text-base text-white/65 md:text-lg">
        The things prospects ask us most before kicking off a software build.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-3xl divide-y divide-white/10 border-y border-white/10">
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <details class="group faq-item">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-start justify-between gap-6 py-6 transition-colors hover:text-gold-soft md:py-7">
            <span class="font-display text-lg font-medium leading-snug md:text-xl">{f.q}</span>
            <span class="mt-1 flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-white/15 text-gold-soft transition-all duration-300 group-open:rotate-45 group-open:border-gold-soft/60 group-open:bg-gold-soft/10" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" class="h-3 w-3">
                <path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="pb-6 pr-12 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/65 md:pb-7 md:text-base">{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-item[open] summary { color: rgb(224 198 123 / 0.95); }
</style>
